      • getSize

        public int getSize()
        Returns the size in memory for this element. Since every primitive element has a size of 1 word, it either returns 1 or the number of elements in an array for variables. For functions this method returns the size that needs to be reserved on the stack.
        Returns:
        Size in memory for this element.
